3.2 Model 4 — sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2 (Embeddings)

sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2
Provider: Hugging Face Inference API   |   Tier: Free tier   |   Speed: Fast — lightweight model

Best for BRAUDLE: Semantic answer similarity — checks if student answer means the same as correct answer without an LLM call

This is the biggest cost saver in the entire stack. Instead of calling an LLM to evaluate every student answer, you compare vector representations mathematically. Zero LLM cost for MCQ and short answer evaluation.

Scenario	Without Embeddings	With Embeddings
Student writes 'the powerhouse of the cell'	LLM call needed to understand it means mitochondria	Similarity score 0.91 vs 'mitochondria produces ATP' — CORRECT detected
Student writes 'mitochondria'	LLM call needed	Similarity score 0.94 — CORRECT instantly
Student writes 'the nucleus'	LLM call needed	Similarity score 0.21 — WRONG instantly
100 MCQ evaluations	100 Groq API calls	0 Groq API calls — pure math

// Similarity thresholds for BRAUDLE
const SIMILARITY = {
  CORRECT: 0.85,   // above this = student understands
  PARTIAL: 0.60,   // between these = partially right
  WRONG:   0.00,   // below 0.60 = wrong
} as const;

export async function checkAnswerSimilarity(
  studentAnswer: string,
  correctAnswer: string
): Promise<'correct' | 'partial' | 'wrong'> {
  const result = await hf.sentenceSimilarity({
    model: 'sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2',
    inputs: {
      source_sentence: correctAnswer,
      sentences: [studentAnswer]
    }
  });

  const score = result[0];
  if (score >= SIMILARITY.CORRECT) return 'correct';
  if (score >= SIMILARITY.PARTIAL)  return 'partial';
  return 'wrong';
}

3.3 Model 5 — google/flan-t5-large (Classification)

google/flan-t5-large
Provider: Hugging Face Inference API   |   Tier: Free tier   |   Speed: Fast — small focused model

Best for BRAUDLE: Zero-shot answer classification — labels student answers without needing a large LLM

Used as a fallback when embeddings alone are not sufficient — for example when the student gives a long theory answer that needs intent classification not just similarity.

export async function classifyStudentAnswer(
  studentAnswer: string,
  correctAnswer: string
): Promise<string> {
  const result = await hf.zeroShotClassification({
    model: 'facebook/bart-large-mnli',
    inputs: `Student answered: ${studentAnswer}. Correct answer: ${correctAnswer}`,
    parameters: {
      candidate_labels: [
        'correct and complete',
        'partially correct',
        'incorrect',
        'off topic'
      ]
    }
  });
  return result.labels[0];
}

3.4 Full Hugging Face Service — src/services/huggingface.service.ts
import { HfInference } from '@huggingface/inference';

const hf = new HfInference(process.env.HUGGINGFACE_API_KEY);

// HF Models
export const HF_MODELS = {
  embeddings:     'sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2',
  classification: 'facebook/bart-large-mnli',
} as const;

// Answer similarity — replaces LLM for evaluation
export async function checkAnswerSimilarity(
  studentAnswer: string,
  correctAnswer: string
): Promise<'correct' | 'partial' | 'wrong'> {
  const result = await hf.sentenceSimilarity({
    model: HF_MODELS.embeddings,
    inputs: { source_sentence: correctAnswer, sentences: [studentAnswer] }
  });
  const score = result[0];
  if (score >= 0.85) return 'correct';
  if (score >= 0.60) return 'partial';
  return 'wrong';
}

// Zero-shot classification for theory answers
export async function classifyStudentAnswer(
  studentAnswer: string,
  correctAnswer: string
): Promise<string> {
  const result = await hf.zeroShotClassification({
    model: HF_MODELS.classification,
    inputs: `Student: ${studentAnswer} | Expected: ${correctAnswer}`,
    parameters: {
      candidate_labels: ['correct','partially correct','incorrect','unclear']
    }
  });
  return result.labels[0];
}

3.5 Hugging Face Cold Start Warning
WARNING	HF Inference API free tier models 'sleep' when not in use. First call after inactivity takes 20-30 seconds to wake up. BRAUDLE handles this by running HF calls in background queues — never in real-time session flows where the student is waiting.

Image OCR runs in BullMQ background queue — cold start is invisible to student. Embeddings for pre-uploaded documents are computed during document processing — not during live sessions.
 
