7.3 Conversation History Trimming
Every Groq call includes conversation history. History grows with every message. You pay in tokens for every message you send. Trim aggressively.

// src/utils/promptBuilder.ts
export function trimConversationHistory(
  messages: Message[]
): Message[] {
  const systemPrompt = messages[0];  // ALWAYS keep — never trim
  const history      = messages.slice(1);

  // Keep last 8 exchanges (16 messages) only
  // Students never reference things said 8+ exchanges ago
  const recent = history.slice(-16);

  return [systemPrompt, ...recent];
}

// Why 16 messages (8 exchanges)?
// Average token count per message: ~150 tokens
// 16 messages = ~2,400 tokens of history
// System prompt = ~200 tokens
// Chunk content = ~600 tokens
// Total context sent: ~3,200 tokens — very efficient

7.4 The 5 Rules That Keep BRAUDLE Free
Rule	What It Means	Savings
Cache before calling	Check Redis before every Groq call. No exceptions.	60-70% fewer Groq calls for foundation cohorts
Right model for right job	Embeddings for evaluation. Smart model for teaching only.	40-50% fewer smart model calls
Trim conversation history	Last 8 exchanges only. Never send full history.	30-40% fewer tokens per call
Short system prompts	Under 200 tokens. No fluff, no repetition.	10-15% fewer tokens per call
No background AI calls	AI only called when student is actively waiting. Never automated.	Eliminates all unnecessary calls
 
